CAMPYLOBACTERIOSIS - USA (02): (PENNSYLVANIA, MARYLAND) UNPASTEURIZED MILK
**************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Mon 30 Jan 2012
Source: abc27/WHTM [edited]
http://www.abc27.com/story/16634572/raw-milk-suspected-of-sickening-12-people


Pennsylvania health officials say there has been an increase in the number of people reporting illnesses since consuming raw milk from a Franklin County farm. The Health Department said Mon 30 Jan 2012, that they have now confirmed 12 cases of _Campylobacter_ infection in Pennsylvania and Maryland.

Officials are awaiting test results on the raw milk sold by The Family Cow store in Chambersburg [Pennsylvania], but said all of those sickened bought raw milk from the store. Raw milk is milk that has not been pasteurized.

A formal recall has not been announced, but officials have recommended that people throw out any raw milk bought from the store after 1 Jan 2012. The farm has voluntarily suspended raw milk production.

[Byline: Myles Snyder]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[It is not clear if the 6 newly reported cases are now confirmed cases previously with cultures pending or if these are truly new cases. The following is the number of outbreaks of enteric infection related to raw milk which have been posted by ProMED-mail starting in 2003:
_Campylobacter_: 11
_Salmonella_: 5
_E. coli_ O157: 5
Q fever: 1
- Mod.LL]
